	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				For those who are constantly comparing wizards and magicians, please take a moment to consider that the strength of a particular class is not measured by it's ability to duel any other class.  Nothing irritates me more when people insist on &quot;proving themselves&quot; against the &quot;masters of damage&quot;.  <BR>
<BR>
For all the mages out there who are consumed with their obsession to outdo wizards, please give it a rest.  Step outside of your ego for a moment, and consider what you are saying.  Since when is a mage with a pet an even match for a lone wizard?  I cannot tell you the number of times that I have dueled people, and they INSIST that it be toe-to-toe.  They seem to think that they have the right to ask that the dueling wizard not use evasive spells or tactics (yonder and invisibility being the two most argued).  <BR>
<BR>
Unfortunately, wizards are not suited well to dueling other casters.  Against melee fighters, there is almost no way that you are going to lose (unless you do not know what you are doing).  I have repeatedly dueled warriors without taking a bit of damage.  It can take upward of 10 minutes to kill them, but I have never been in danger of losing.  But throw me up against a shaman of equal level, a mage, an enchanter, a necromancer, a druid, etc., etc. and I am almost always guaranteed to lose.<BR>
<BR>
Mages, realize that you have a pet, realize that you have debuffs, and DoTs.  In addition, you have DDs that do just about the same damage as a wizard of equal level.  Wizards have DD and nothing more.  Mages, I say this... with a pet, and DoTs and equally potent DDs, you had better not lose a duel.  If that happens, you clearly have no idea how to play the class.  But, when you win a duel against the unbalanced wizard, do not go strutting about like a pea**** with the pretense that you won based on any measure of personal skill.  Mages are simply better suited to duels.  Wizards only shine when they have the support of friends.  Don't try to read into it, that is the truth.  Mages would fare much worse if they had no pets.<BR>
<BR>
For those who disagree that a pet class dueling a wizard is not 2 against one, then by all means, let me duel you while I bring my warrior friend along as my pet.  I will even make sure he is only level 30.  Fair?<BR>
<BR>
Mages, realize that you are inferior where it really counts... against high-level mobs, and this is why you have pets and debuffs and utility spells.  They exist to give you some use in a group when you are unable to do any magical damage.  This is not a personal attack on your playing style, it is a limitation of your class.  Most people have the notion that wizards and mages are the same class, only one has pets and one has gates, but this is not the case.  Realize that each has strengths and weaknesses, and at different times within the game.  Stop the bickering over which is superior and which is inferior -- there is no correct answer.<BR>
<BR>
Cobal Tyrchiylde<BR>
Mithaniel Marr
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
